        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 7:37PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 736 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Crossville, or 7 miles east of Boaz, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40-50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lebanon, Dog Town, Collbran, Arona, Kilpatrick, Rodentown,
Crossville, Lathamville, and Fort Payne.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
northeastern Alabama.</instruction>
